His name means heavenly —supremely good and profoundly ethereal. He tranquilized me with his voice; my favorite music. Mine means flower —dainty but thrives every season to grow. I love to sow bright seeds to his soul; he loves it when I do. We synced up. We teamed up. We made subtitles for the language we didn’t understand. But he happened to get drained too easily these past few days, and he needed longer time to recharge. Still, I love him even if the sky gets bluer on his side. But I would love it better if we create yellow as we collide.
